main event: A civilian reported seeing an unidentified flying object over Cincinnati, Ohio on April 30, 1969.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10 minutes.
The observer could not clearly identify the object, but saw it come over the trees about 2 miles away.
The observer was sent a questionnaire on July 11, 1969 to obtain more details, but it had not been returned as of December 1, 1969.
The report states that only sketchy information was available on the sighting.
The report mentions that the information was somewhat conflicting in that the observer could not see the object clearly.
sighted object: one unidentified object in the sky
